          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12699340/comment/13924074",
            "id": "13924074",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=kkambatl",
              "name": "kkambatl",
              "key": "kkambatl",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Karthik Kambatla",
              "active": false,
              "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
            },
            "body": "Just to understand what we are trying to address here. [~sunilg] - is the following an accurate description - when multiple tasks query the LocalDirAllocator, allocation is based on the capacity available at that point in time and does not take previous queries into consideration, leading to potential over-commit of disk space.\n\nIf yes, just adding a cut-off only delays the onset of this problem. A better approach might be to \"reserve\" disk-space for a duration of time. ",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=kkambatl",
              "name": "kkambatl",
              "key": "kkambatl",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Karthik Kambatla",
              "active": false,
              "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
            },
            "created": "2014-03-07T17:23:00.421+0000",
            "updated": "2014-03-07T17:23:00.421+0000"
          },
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12699340/comment/13925465",
            "id": "13925465",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=sunilg",
              "name": "sunilg",
              "key": "sunilg",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Sunil G",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Asia/Kolkata"
            },
            "body": "Yes Karthik. Existing logic is not considering the previously assigned space for the same local directory assignment.\nThis scenario will be exposed while many tasks were asking for the path at same time.\nFor eg, Task1 may have granted with 100MB to write and started its writing, but may be within fraction of second Task2 came for a 80MB to write.\nSame path will be given Task2 based on Free space at that point of time. At this time, may be Task1 would have finished only 10MB of its write.\nAnd 90MB may be still to be written. This delta of 90MB is not considered while allocating space for Task2.\n\n\"A better approach might be to 'reserve' disk-space for a duration of time\"\nWith this approach a small problem will be like calculating \"disk speed of write\". \"time remaining\" to be derived for a task for its local write.\nAnd also to derive a factor \"how much is written\" and \"how much more to be written\" at a given time for a task.\n\nGiven the disk write speed as a configuration (based on disk type, rpm etc), these factors can be derived. And allotted space for a task can also be considered.\nThis can almost solve the problem. Please share your thoughts on this approach.",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=sunilg",
              "name": "sunilg",
              "key": "sunilg",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Sunil G",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Asia/Kolkata"
            },
            "created": "2014-03-10T05:45:55.580+0000",
            "updated": "2014-03-10T05:45:55.580+0000"
          },
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12699340/comment/13935431",
            "id": "13935431",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=kkambatl",
              "name": "kkambatl",
              "key": "kkambatl",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Karthik Kambatla",
              "active": false,
              "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
            },
            "body": "bq. Given the disk write speed as a configuration (based on disk type, rpm etc), these factors can be derived. And allotted space for a task can also be considered.\nSounds reasonable. ",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=kkambatl",
